page.title: 11ARCHITECTURE IN SUDBOROUGH
page.content: In Sudborough the houses are all fairly old except for a few which were built in the late sixties and early seventies. There are several thatched cottages in Sudborough. There are also some terraced houses, all in the same style,one containing a pub. These houses are made of a pale stone and brick, which makes Sudborough a nice village of pleasant houses. Since the by-pass was opened on the A6116 a few years ago, Sudborough has become extremely quiet - the residents mostly hope that it will remain this way!
